# Configuration for running the GitHub Actions workflows locally with
# nektos/act (https://github.com/nektos/act). Used as a stopgap for CI until the
# repository is public (free Actions) or Actions billing is enabled.
#
# Map GitHub's `ubuntu-latest` to a runner image that ships the basics the
# smoke-tests workflow needs (apt, curl, git, sudo, node). cmake/ninja are
# installed by the workflow itself.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Keep build caches (actions/cache) and the apt/cargo work between runs so the
# expensive DuckDB archive build only happens once.
--reuse
